I want to move some notes I took on SICP to this repo. I also want to integrate my notes with the templating system I use to write these entries. That way, I can still pipe the file into the âœ³=(in-code "racket")ðŸ”š cli for evaluation while also gaining the ability to render the prose using the features I've developed atop âœ³=(in-code "comb")ðŸ”š.

I think the best way to do so is to turn them into a lightweight literate programming format like âœ³=(in-code "lit")ðŸ”š. However, I don't want my ability to execute this code to depend on my understanding of âœ³=(in-code "awk")ðŸ”š - I want to keep as much as possible in a single language. So I'll replicate the features of âœ³=(in-code "lit")ðŸ”š using âœ³=(in-code "babashka")ðŸ”š. I haven't used it yet, and it seems like a decent enough exercise to get going with it.

